================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

This codebase incorporates and/or builds on the following third-party software.
Each component retains its original license; see the individual project's
license file for the full terms.

* Physical Intelligence openpi (https://github.com/Physical-Intelligence/openpi)
  Apache License 2.0
  Used as the underlying pi_0.5 VLA codebase. The src/openpi/ tree is derived
  from openpi with modifications for InSight (additional training configs,
  policies, and training loops; see commit history).

* LIBERO (https://github.com/Lifelong-Robot-Learning/LIBERO)
  MIT License
  Used as the simulation benchmark for the block-flip and drawer-close
  experiments. We rely on the libero-insight fork
  (https://github.com/insight-vla/libero-insight), which adds drawer-primitive
  BDDLs on top of upstream LIBERO.

* LeRobot (https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot)
  Apache License 2.0
  Dataset format and loaders used by both simulation and real-robot training
  pipelines.

* Gemma (https://ai.google.dev/gemma)
  Gemma Terms of Use + Gemma Prohibited Use Policy
  Backbone weights used by pi_0.5. Gemma weights are NOT distributed with this
  repository and are subject to Google's Gemma Terms.

* Gemini 3 Flash API (https://ai.google.dev/)
  Subject to Google's API terms of service
  Used as the planner / skill-gap proposer / oracle VLM at runtime; not
  distributed with this repository.

================================================================================
External baseline (not vendored)
================================================================================

* CaP-X (https://capgym.github.io/, https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.22435)
  Fu et al. CaP-X is used as a Code-as-Policy baseline in the paper's
  twist / pour / composition experiments. The CaP-X codebase itself is NOT
  vendored in this repository; install it separately from its upstream
  source. The InSight-side evaluation harness used to run the comparison
  is described in the paper appendix.
